the bed is unmade.{pg}it always is.
NAME bed dialog

DLG tv
the tv is static.{pg}you don't turn it off.
NAME tv dialog

DLG as
the ashtray is fuller than it should be.
NAME ashtray dialog

DLG ch
your jacket is on the chair.{pg}you'll need it.
NAME chair dialog

DLG wn
rain on the glass.{pg}the streetlight is the only color outside.
NAME window dialog

DLG fn
the ceiling fan is still broken.{pg}it just clicks.
NAME fan dialog

DLG mr
you catch your reflection.{pg}you don't recognize tonight's face.
NAME mirror dialog

DLG sk
the faucet drips.{pg}you've been meaning to fix it.
NAME sink dialog

DLG cl
the calendar still says last month.
NAME calendar dialog

DLG ph
the voicemail light is blinking.{pg}you don't press play.
NAME phone dialog

DLG nb
"you got a light?"{pg}"..."{pg}"watch yourself out there tonight."
NAME neighbor dialog

DLG fg
"spare anything?"{pg}"...didn't think so."
NAME figure dialog

DLG rt
it doesn't look at you.
NAME rat dialog

DLG ct
"..."{pg}it watches you go.
NAME cat dialog

DLG dl
"you're late."{pg}"you got the money?"{pg}"...yeah."{pg}"don't look at me like that."{pg}"everybody who comes here looks at me like that."{pg}he holds out his hand.{pg}you put forty dollars in it.{pg}"breathe through it. don't take it all at once."{pg}"and don't come back tomorrow."{pg}you both know you'll come back tomorrow.{pg}home, after.{pg}the ceiling fan is still broken.
NAME dealer dialog

DLG i0
forty bucks.{pg}enough.
NAME cash dialog

DLG i1
a polaroid.{pg}someone you used to love.{pg}you put it face-down again.
NAME photo dialog

DLG i2
you pocket the lighter.
NAME lighter dialog

DLG i3
empty.{pg}of course.
NAME bottle dialog
